<div id="ta188_85" class="block iDevice_content">
<div class="dentro_contenidos" style="display: block;" id="pagina_1">
<p>In this exercise students will face an <b>open cloze</b>, again to check their lexical and lexico-grammatical knowledge.</p>
<p>Students have to fill 12 gaps in a modified cloze, but in this case no items are provided to choose from.</p>
<p>Tips:</p>
<ul>
<li>First read the text quickly to get an idea of what it is about.</li>
<li>Look at the words before and after the gap and decide what type of word fits best.</li>
<li>You will usually need “grammar words”, that is, articles, prepositions, auxiliary verbs, pronouns or conjunctions.</li>
<li>Words may be part of fixed phrases or collocations.</li>
<li>Answer the questions you find easy first and don’t leave any gaps blank. If you don’t know the answer, guess.</li>
</ul>
